02/03/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Synod of the Serbian Orthodox Church (SPC) announced on Monday (March 1st) it has decided to postpone until the autumn the official enthronement ceremony for new Serbian Patriarch Irinej.
The enthronement was supposed to take place on April 25th at the Patriarchy in Pec, Kosovo.
No new date has been announced.
Bishop Irinej of Nis was elected on January 22nd.
(B92, Beta, RTS - 01/03/10)
